Loading Dim_Contract - Updating Existing Records 8

·         For Updating the already existing records Drag and Drop Second LookUp below the first LookUp

·      Drag the Blue arrow and place it on Top of Lookup

·         To rename the Look up --- > Right Click on Lookup --- > Click Rename and Change the name to

         (Lookup – only Non-Matching records will pass through)



           ·         After renaming Lookup will appear with new name as below

           

          ·         Double Click on LookUp – Only non-matching records will pass through ---- > Lookup Transformation Editor will pop up.

          ·         In the Editor, Click the Drop Down of the Specify how to handle rows with no matching entries ---- >  Choose             
            Redirect Rows to no match output and Click Connection

         

         ·                     In Connection Click on Drop down of OLE DB Connection manager ---- > Choose the Destination Database                    
                     (Mortgage Datamart) ----- > Click OK

         

         ·         Click on the Drop Down of Use a Table or a View option and Choose the Target Table(Dim_Contract)

         ·         Click on the Columns at Left side of Lookup Editor

         

         ·         In mappings make sure all the columns are mapped. There are no mappings for Contract Key, Created at,        
          modified at because they will be populated automatically through SQL Server ------ >  Click OK.





            ·     ·                     Drag and Drop and OLE DB Command to the Canvas ---> Drag the Blue Arrow towards the 
                     OLE DB Command to make the connection. Another Wizard will pop up.

                  

                 ·                     In the Wizard, Choose Look up No Match Output and click OK

                   

                 ·                     Double click on the OLE DB Command a Dialog Box appears as below

                 

                ·         In Connection Manager, Choose the Destination Database (Mortgage Datamart connection)     ---- >
        Click Component Properties.

                 

                ·         Run the Stored Procedure from Code File in SQL Server Management Studio.

       ·         To Open the file, Double Click or Right Click on the File that you downloaded ----- > Click Open

        

        ·         The script for Stored Procedure will open in SQL Server Management studio-----> Click Execute. 
          Message shows Command executed successfully .

        

        ·         Execute this Stored Procedure in sql command of Component Properties in OLE DB Command

         Copy this Script: EXEC [dbo].[USP_UpdateDim_Contract] ?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?



·      Click Column Mappings to map the Columns

 ·         Click the Drop Down of Input Columns and Choose the Corresponding Columns so that it will matches         
            with Destination Columns (example : ContractDate ---- > @ContractDate). Similarly Choose for all the Columns

          


        
 

·          ·  Once mapped all the Columns ---- > Click OK


 ·        · Finally, Package looks like below.
